to disrespect any of that with a lie.

244
00:18:35,708 --> 00:18:36,708
[chuckles]

245
00:18:37,208 --> 00:18:38,583
This is all your fault.

246
00:18:38,666 --> 00:18:41,125
You're easy to talk to,
and you're kind of cute.

247
00:18:42,791 --> 00:18:43,875
Anyway,

248
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,625
it's time for me to stop.

249
00:18:47,958 --> 00:18:49,958
I know I'm not making sense right now.

250
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:54,416
I'm sorry.

251
00:19:02,666 --> 00:19:04,500
No, I understand what you're saying.

252
00:19:11,291 --> 00:19:12,458
That being said,

253
00:19:14,166 --> 00:19:15,916
I'm grateful for our time together.

254
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:18,666
Bye now, Yusuke.

255
00:19:19,708 --> 00:19:20,875
[chuckles]

256
00:19:24,250 --> 00:19:25,208
Will you…

257
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:28,791
please take care of him?

258
00:20:03,125 --> 00:20:05,125
[emotional piano music continues]

259
00:20:20,250 --> 00:20:21,791
[music fades]

260
00:20:21,875 --> 00:20:23,583
-Sorry to interrupt, Midori.
-Hmm?

261
00:20:23,666 --> 00:20:26,541
I was hoping to discuss something
with you. Do you have a minute?

262
00:20:28,375 --> 00:20:29,458
What's up?

263
00:20:37,291 --> 00:20:38,458
Ah…

264
00:20:39,791 --> 00:20:40,875
You say you wanna discuss,

265
00:20:40,958 --> 00:20:43,541
but the look on your face says
you've already decided.

266
00:20:44,708 --> 00:20:45,750
What?

267
00:20:47,208 --> 00:20:50,583
I love when women have that look.
It's beautiful.

268
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:55,083
However, as president,

269
00:20:55,166 --> 00:20:57,625
I don't think I'm looking forward
to hearing this.

270
00:20:58,791 --> 00:20:59,916
All right.

271
00:21:01,666 --> 00:21:03,000
So what now?

272
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:06,291
Do you wanna treat me to lunch, hmm?

273
00:21:07,916 --> 00:21:08,875
That sounds nice.

274
00:21:10,458 --> 00:21:11,375
Well, then.

275
00:21:13,083 --> 00:21:14,041
I accept.

276
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,291
Thank you very much.

277
00:21:18,583 --> 00:21:20,583
[emotional piano music resumes]

278
00:21:23,291 --> 00:21:24,666
[man] We should be all set.

279
00:21:25,166 --> 00:21:26,500
What do you feel like?

280
00:21:36,666 --> 00:21:37,750
Shinoda.

281
00:21:37,833 --> 00:21:38,708
Oh.

282
00:21:39,625 --> 00:21:41,791
Hey. Which would you choose?

283
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:56,500
[music fades]

284
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:01,166
Mm. I'd go with this one.

285
00:22:01,750 --> 00:22:02,958
I thought so.

286
00:22:04,041 --> 00:22:05,416
-Hey.
-[man] Yes.

287
00:22:06,208 --> 00:22:08,500
-[Shinoda] Let's roast them.
-[man] I'll get it ready.

288
00:22:14,625 --> 00:22:15,833
[sighs]

289
00:22:30,166 --> 00:22:32,166
[brakes squeal]

290
00:23:12,083 --> 00:23:14,875
[whistle blowing]

291
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:23,791
[melancholy music playing]

292
00:23:24,583 --> 00:23:26,541
[woman] Hi there. I'm your new contact.

293
00:23:27,041 --> 00:23:30,583
My name is Kashiwagi.
Akane Inc. sent me. It's nice to meet you.

294
00:23:30,666 --> 00:23:32,500
Nice to meet you too. I'm Naruse.

295
00:23:33,541 --> 00:23:35,500
This is a nice café space you've got.

296
00:23:36,875 --> 00:23:39,333
[Kazu] Thank you.
We couldn't have done it without you all.

297
00:23:42,958 --> 00:23:44,125
I, uh…

298
00:23:44,208 --> 00:23:45,166
Yes?

299
00:23:47,833 --> 00:23:49,666
Oh, nothing.

300
00:23:50,375 --> 00:23:52,750
-I look forward to working with you.
-Likewise.

301
00:23:55,916 --> 00:23:59,625
Hi, nice to meet you. I'm Kashiwagi.
I'll be taking over for Saeko.

302
00:23:59,708 --> 00:24:01,833
-Nice to meet you.
-[Kashiwagi] Nice to meet you.

303
00:24:04,208 --> 00:24:06,083
What have you got here? It's gorgeous!

304
00:24:06,166 --> 00:24:08,250
I know, right? It's fantastic.

305
00:24:08,333 --> 00:24:09,833
[Saeko gasps]

306
00:24:09,916 --> 00:24:11,666
-[Kazu] Huh?
-Huh?

307
00:24:11,750 --> 00:24:14,541
-[melancholy music continues]
-[inaudible dialogue]

308
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:29,500
[melancholy music continues]

309
00:25:12,666 --> 00:25:15,333
Even your heart isn't enough
to keep me alive.

310
00:25:17,750 --> 00:25:18,708
I'm sorry.

311
00:25:24,625 --> 00:25:25,625
What do I…

312
00:25:33,375 --> 00:25:35,041
What do you think I should do?

313
00:25:45,708 --> 00:25:47,750
What would you like me to do, Yusuke…

314
00:25:53,083 --> 00:25:54,375
with the time I have?

315
00:25:58,208 --> 00:26:00,208
[music fades]

316
00:27:09,666 --> 00:27:10,916
[sighs] Okay.

317
00:27:48,791 --> 00:27:50,791
[footsteps approaching]

318
00:28:10,541 --> 00:28:11,541
[door opens]

319
00:28:14,416 --> 00:28:15,458
[door closes]

